# Testing Strategy & Patterns

## Test Structure

```typescript
describe("Service.method", () => {
  let mockRepository: jest.Mocked<Repository>;

  beforeEach(() => {
    mockRepository = createMockRepository();
  });

  it("should return data when conditions are met", async () => {
    // Arrange
    const input = { id: 1 };
    mockRepository.find.mockResolvedValue(testData);

    // Act
    const result = await service.method(input);

    // Assert
    expect(result).toHaveProperty("data");
    expect(mockRepository.find).toHaveBeenCalledWith(input.id);
  });

  it("should throw error when data not found", async () => {
    // Arrange
    mockRepository.find.mockResolvedValue(null);

    // Act & Assert
    await expect(service.method({ id: 1 }))
      .rejects.toThrow("Not found");
  });
});
```

## Coverage Requirements
- Critical business logic: 90%+
- API handlers: 80%+
- Utilities: 70%+
- UI components: 50%+

## Test Naming Pattern
```
✓ should [expected behavior] when [condition]
✓ should throw [error] when [condition]
✓ should call [dependency] with [parameters] when [condition]
```
